Building a shell

Features:
1) "exit" and ctrl+D to quit the shell
2) "cd"+directory to change a directory, "cd ~" to change to home
3) "jobs" to list current jobs
4) "kill %i" to kill the no.i job
5) "bg %i" to put the no.i job running background
6) "fg %i" to put the no.i job running foreground
7) foreground & background execution
8) support pipes
9) ctrl+z to stop a job, ctrl+c to quit a job


Reference:
http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Implementing-a-Shell.html#Implementing-a-Shell
